{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As for the text-based visual question answering (TextVQA) system, to accurately utilize visual objects and optical character recognition (OCR) tokens, (Zhou et al. 2024) pioneered the graph pooling inference network (GPIN).",
    "As an innovative evolutionary graph learning method, GPIN not only purifies the visual entities (objects and tokens), but also deeply captures the core semantics through its unique adaptive node discarding strategy, dual-path hierarchical graph architecture, and the use of graph pooling technique, which brings superior performance to the TextVQA task.",
    "Facing the challenge of matching short texts with long documents, (Zhang et al. 2018b) successfully solved the matching problem brought by texts with different lengths and complex structures by constructing a document keyword graph, combining graph neural network, graph attention mechanism, and efficient graph pooling strategy, which provided a new solution idea in the field of text matching.",
    "In the discourse-level relation extraction (DRE) task, (Hsu et al. 2101) introduced an innovative pooling-non-pooling framework.",
    "Among them, the pooling branch improves the performance of the model by streamlining the graph structure so that the graph neural network can obtain a wider perceptual range in fewer layers."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As for the text-based visual question answering (TextVQA) system, to accurately utilize visual objects and optical character recognition (OCR) tokens, (Zhou et al. 2024) pioneered the graph pooling inference network (GPIN).",
    "Facing the challenge of matching short texts with long documents, (Zhang et al. 2018b) successfully solved the matching problem brought by texts with different lengths and complex structures by constructing a document keyword graph, combining graph neural network, graph attention mechanism, and efficient graph pooling strategy, which provided a new solution idea in the field of text matching.",
    "In the discourse-level relation extraction (DRE) task, (Hsu et al. 2101) introduced an innovative pooling-non-pooling framework."
  ]
